Sunny and Cozy 2-Room Apartment for Sale in Jugla

The apartment is located on the 5th floor of a brick building (no elevator) and has a total area of 42 m². Originally, one room was walk-through and the other isolated, but it has now been reconfigured so that both rooms are separate and used as bedrooms. Windows face both sides of the building, providing natural light throughout the day. The kitchen is separate, and the bathroom features a shower. 

The apartment has undergone partial renovation, preserving original interior elements – wooden floors, cast iron radiators, and other authentic details that give the home a unique charm and character. 

Utilities and Amenities:
- City central heating;
- City water supply and sewage;
- Electricity connection. 

Costs:
Utility bills depend on the season and consumption: approx. €200/month in winter, €140/month in summer;
Property tax – approx. €25 per year;
Land lease – approx. €5/month;
Building managed by Rīgas namu pārvaldnieks (RNP). 

Building Description:
Five-story brick building; apartment is on the top (5th) floor (no elevator);
Recently renovated roof;
Resident parking available next to the building;
Quiet, peaceful, and friendly neighborhood. 

Location:
The apartment is situated in Jugla – one of Riga’s greenest and most tranquil districts, with well-developed infrastructure and convenient public transport to the city center. The windows offer a lovely view of the Šmerlis Forest and Lake Bābelītis. 

15–20 minutes by car to Riga city center;
Public transport stops (buses, trolleybuses, trams) – 2–5 minutes on foot;
Nearby are shops, schools, kindergartens, and healthcare facilities;
Just a short walk to Lakes Jugla and Bābelītis and beautiful walking areas;
The surrounding environment – forests, lakes, and nature trails – is ideal for peaceful daily living and relaxation in nature. 

A 3D tour is available – explore the apartment remotely before scheduling a live viewing. 

Contact us to arrange a viewing – this apartment could be your new home.

